{"expireTime":9007200804686406000,"key":"transformer-remark-markdown-html-ast-8c888d944c1361fa474d599aca9d9cb1-gatsby-remark-graphvizgatsby-remark-code-titlesgatsby-remark-imagesgatsby-remark-responsive-iframegatsby-remark-autolink-headersgatsby-remark-prismjsgatsby-remark-copy-linked-filesgatsby-remark-smartypants-","val":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Gatsby is more than just a new website framework — creating websites in Gatsby is a fundamentally different paradigm than in a CMS-specific framework.","position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":1,"offset":1},"end":{"line":2,"column":152,"offset":152}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":1,"offset":1},"end":{"line":2,"column":152,"offset":152}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Website teams adopting Gatsby report improved collaboration at each stage — from architecture and user research, to design and development, to testing and launch. Many of these derive from Gatsby features: faster development cycles, easy compatibility with React component libraries, a CMS-agnostic development environment, the ability to easily deploy static build artifacts.","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":1,"offset":154},"end":{"line":4,"column":378,"offset":531}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":1,"offset":154},"end":{"line":4,"column":378,"offset":531}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"To fully take advantage of new, Gatsby-enabled workflows, consider adopting some of these techniques:","position":{"start":{"line":6,"column":1,"offset":533},"end":{"line":6,"column":102,"offset":634}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":6,"column":1,"offset":533},"end":{"line":6,"column":102,"offset":634}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h3","properties":{"id":"architecture"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#architecture","aria-label":"architecture permalink","class":"anchor"},"children":[{"type":"raw","value":"<svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg>"}]},{"type":"text","value":"Architecture","position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":5,"offset":640},"end":{"line":8,"column":17,"offset":652}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":1,"offset":636},"end":{"line":8,"column":17,"offset":652}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"em","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Take advantage of extended evaluation periods to build a component library","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":2,"offset":655},"end":{"line":10,"column":76,"offset":729}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1,"offset":654},"end":{"line":10,"column":77,"offset":730}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1,"offset":654},"end":{"line":10,"column":77,"offset":730}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Larger companies considering adopting Gatsby often plan in terms of migrating multiple sites (or internationalized versions of sites) over a timeframe of a few months to two years. These projects can have long preparation times before active development starts.","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1,"offset":732},"end":{"line":12,"column":262,"offset":993}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1,"offset":732},"end":{"line":12,"column":262,"offset":993}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"One high-leverage activity during these time windows is to focus development on a React component library. Then, when development begins the team is able to quickly assemble Gatsby React pages from these pre-built components. Consider designating senior UI developers as “component architects” in this process.","position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":1,"offset":995},"end":{"line":14,"column":311,"offset":1305}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":1,"offset":995},"end":{"line":14,"column":311,"offset":1305}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"em","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Consider a less-expensive CMS or multi-modal architecture","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":2,"offset":1308},"end":{"line":16,"column":59,"offset":1365}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1,"offset":1307},"end":{"line":16,"column":60,"offset":1366}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1,"offset":1307},"end":{"line":16,"column":60,"offset":1366}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Choosing Gatsby frees your CMS from doing a lot of the heavy lifting, such as scaling to meet peak load and having a rich, modern web development experience. If you’re using an expensive enterprise CMS, Gatsby can help your project stay within budget by allowing you to choose a simpler, cheaper option, such as a hosted Drupal instance, or a content management SaaS like Contentful.","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1,"offset":1368},"end":{"line":18,"column":384,"offset":1751}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1,"offset":1368},"end":{"line":18,"column":384,"offset":1751}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"childr